-- CEZ Turkish Partner Akkok to Invest $780 Million, Dunya Reports
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2011-12-26T07:53:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/cez-turkish-partner-akkok-to-invest-780-million-dunya-reports.html
Akkok Group, which co-owns energy
utility  Akenerji Elektrik Uretim AS (AKENR)  with the Czech Republic’s
 CEZ AS (CEZ) , plans to invest $780 million in 2012,  Dunya  reported,
citing Chief Executive Officer Mehmet Ali Berkman.  About half the Istanbul-based group’s investment will be in
energy and one-third in real estate, the newspaper reported.  Akenerji, in which CEZ and Akkok dropped plans to sell
their respective stakes of 37.5 percent each, intends to raise
its power production capacity to 2,000 megawatts in 2013 from
659 megawatts at the end of this year, Berkman told the
newspaper.  Akkok group invested $500 million in 2011, Berkman also
told Dunya .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 